                    │\n│               │                                 │ discovered for a recurring task. Also      │                       │\n│               │                                 │ review learnings before major tasks.       │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 📜 session-logs                 │ Search and analyze your own session logs   │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ (older/parent conversations) using jq.     │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🔉 sherpa-onnx-tts              │ Local text-to-speech via sherpa-onnx       │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ (offline, no cloud)                        │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📦 skill-creator                │ Guide for creating effective skills. This  │ openclaw-workspace    │\n│               │                                 │ skill should be used when users want to    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ create a new skill (or update an existing  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ skill) that extends Claude's capabilities  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ with specialized knowledge, workflows, or  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ tool integrations.                         │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📦 skill-vetter                 │ Security-first skill vetting for AI        │ openclaw-workspace    │\n│               │                                 │ agents. Use before installing any skill    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ from ClawdHub, GitHub, or other sources.   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ Checks for red flags, permission scope,    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ and suspicious patterns.                   │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 💬 slack                        │ Use when you need to control Slack from    │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ OpenClaw via the slack tool, including     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ reacting to messages or pinning/unpinning  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ items in Slack channels or DMs.            │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🌊 songsee                      │ Generate spectrograms and feature-panel    │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ visualizations from audio with the         │                       │\n│               │                                 │ songsee CLI.                               │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🔊 sonoscli                     │ Control Sonos speakers (discover/status/   │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ play/volume/group).                        │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🎵 spotify-player               │ Terminal Spotify playback/search via       │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ spogo (preferred) or spotify_player.       │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📦 summarize                    │ Summarize URLs or files with the           │ openclaw-workspace    │\n│               │                                 │ summarize CLI (web, PDFs, images, audio,   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ YouTube).                                  │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 🪝 taskflow                     │ Use when work should span one or more      │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ detached tasks but still behave like one   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ job with a single owner context. TaskFlow  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ is the durable flow substrate under        │                       │\n│               │                                 │ authoring layers like Lobster, ACPX,       │                       │\n│               │                                 │ plugins, or plain code. Keep conditional   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ logic in the caller; use TaskFlow for      │                       │\n│               │                                 │ flow identity, child-task linkage,         │                       │\n│               │                                 │ waiting state, revision-checked            │                       │\n│               │                                 │ mutations, and user-facing emergence.      │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📥 taskflow-inbox-triage        │ Example TaskFlow authoring pattern for     │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ inbox triage. Use when messages need       │                       │\n│               │                                 │ different treatment based on intent, with  │                       │\n│               │                                 │ some routes notifying immediately, some    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ waiting on outside answers, and others     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ rolling into a later summary.              │                       │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📦 tavily-search                │ Web search via Tavily API (alternative to  │ openclaw-workspace    │\n│               │                                 │ Brave). Use when the user asks to search   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ the web / look up sources / find links     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ and Brave web_search is unavailable or     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ undesired. Returns a small set of          │                       │\n│               │                                 │ relevant results (title, url, snippet)     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ and can optionally include short answer    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ summaries.                                 │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ ✅ things-mac                   │ Manage Things 3 via the `things` CLI on    │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ macOS (add/update projects+todos via URL   │                       │\n│               │                                 │ scheme; read/search/list from the local    │                       │\n│               │                                 │ Things database). Use when a user asks     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ OpenClaw to add a task to Things, list     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ inbox/today/upcoming, search tasks, or     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ inspect projects/areas/tags.               │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🧵 tmux                         │ Remote-control tmux sessions for           │ openclaw-bundled      │\n│               │                                 │ interactive CLIs by sending keystrokes     │                       │\n│               │                                 │ and scraping pane output.                  │                       │\n│ △ needs setup │ 📋 trello                       │ Manage Tre